The paper discusses deep multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that deals with multiple agents interacting in an environment. The paper also discusses the use of value-based methods and quantile estimators, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions the importance of stability and convergence, which are topics in control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
